  "body": "We need to find blocks containing incoming/outgoing txs for a specific address. These must include both ETH and ERC-20 transactions.\n\nIn order to minimize the number of requests done through Infura's JSON-RPC API, we should:\n\n- first find a range of blocks containing minimum 20 outgoing ETH txs by performing binary search using `eth_getTransactionCount`. This will give us `[fromBlock, toBlock]` range\n- find a seq of block numbers by binary search inside `[fromBlock, toBlock]` using `eth_getBalance` calls\n- as above will only give us blocks containing txs with ETH transfers, we need to invoke `eth_getLogs` twice (for both incoming and outgoing txs) in order to find all blocks containing ERC-20 txs. For this we pass `fromBlock`, `toBlock` and `topics` params to `eth_getLogs` invocation\n- merge ETH and ERC-20 block IDs and store these inside a database\n\nThis implements bullets 1 - 4 from https://notes.status.im/EDU-Tri6TbextQ2rt5P6yA?view",
